Here’s how to use each of the four EVORCA logo variants across the brand touchpoints.

Logo 1 – Clean Wordmark (EVORCA)
Use: Primary app and product identity.

Best for: App header, web navbar, login/landing hero, invoices, email signatures, social profile names.

Rationale: The customised “O” with subtle QR/gate motif directly communicates “smart, verified entry” while staying minimal and premium.

Backgrounds: Light or softly tinted surfaces; avoid very busy photo backgrounds so the editorial feel remains clear.

Logo 2 – Layered Card Icon + Wordmark
Use: Splash screens, marketing, and hero visuals.

Best for: Mobile app splash, onboarding screens, marketing posters, web hero section, presentation covers.

Rationale: The layered invitation-card icon echoes your design system’s “curated atmosphere” and tonal depth, so it feels like a premium event invite, not a generic SaaS.

Backgrounds: Gradient teal, teal→primary-container gradients, or soft photo backdrops related to events.

Logo 3 – Circular QR + Check Emblem
Use: Functional product contexts where verification matters.

Best for: Gate scanner screen badge, QR pass watermark, “Verified by EVORCA” seal on passes and tickets, small app sections like “Check-in,” “Attendance,” or “Security.”

Rationale: The circular symbol reads as trust, completion, and security, matching flows like check-in success, gate status, and fraud-free entry.

Backgrounds: Dark gate mode UI, inverse-surface or surface-container-high; it will pop cleanly there.

Logo 4 – EV Monogram (Funnel/Path)
Use: Compact mark where space is tight.

Best for: Favicon, app icon base shape, small corner bugs on dashboards, internal tools, avatar circles, and social media icons.

Rationale: The E/V path suggests RSVPs flowing through a funnel into successful events, which fits analytics, dashboards, and growth/story slides.

Backgrounds: Solid teal or gold with white monogram, or white with teal monogram for maximum clarity at tiny sizes.

Specific Use Mapping
App logo (top bar, main brand in UI): Logo 1 (Wordmark) as default; Logo 2 on splash or landing.

Splash screen: Logo 2 centered, with gradient teal background and subtle editorial spacing.

Favicon / browser tab / small system icons: Logo 4 (monogram only).

Mobile app icon: Logo 4 as main icon; optionally include small EVORCA text only on larger sizes.

Woodwork / physical signage (reception, backdrops, gates):

Large panels: Logo 2 (icon + wordmark).

Minimal plaques or small engraved pieces: Logo 1 or Logo 4 depending on size.

QR passes and gate devices: Logo 3 as a seal/mark near the QR or in the scanner UI header.